The schematic (schematic.sch) was drawn using the gEDA project (http://www.gpleda.org/)

The following libraries are required:
	- LiquidCrystal (included in the Arduino base pakage)
	- DS1307RTC (http://www.pjrc.com/teensy/td_libs_DS1307RTC.html)
	- TimeAlarms (http://www.pjrc.com/teensy/td_libs_TimeAlarms.html)
	- Time (http://www.pjrc.com/teensy/td_libs_Time.html)
	
To install these libraries:

cd /usr/local/arduino-libraries && sudo git clone git@github.com:PaulStoffregen/DS1307RTC.git
cd /usr/local/arduino-libraries && sudo git clone git@github.com:PaulStoffregen/Time.git
cd /usr/local/arduino-libraries && sudo git clone git@github.com:PaulStoffregen/TimeAlarms.git

Then, to build:
make

And finally to upload (make sure the board is plugged in):
sudo make upload

